method.name: emulation_pim_group_config
method.description: This procedure configures Multicast groups added to a PIM session. This allows adding (*,G) or (S,G) entries to PIM session.

description.text: This option defines the action to be taken. Note: modify and delete options are not supported for IxTclProtocol. Valid choices are: create - (default) An existing multicast group pool is associated/linked with the specified PIM session. delete - Remove one group pools from this session clear_all - Removes all group pools from this session. modify - Modifies group pools from this session. enable - Enables the given item provided by -handle. disable - Disables the given item provided by -handle.

choice.choiceText: An existing multicast group/source pool is associated/linked with the specified PIM session. It is also used to add join/prune, sources and crpRanges to a Pim session.
Remove one group pools from this session. Also used to remove join/prunes, sources and crpRanges from Pim session.
Modifies group pools from this session. Also used to modify join/prunes, sources and crpRanges from Pim session.
Removes all group pools from this session. Also removes all join/prunes, sources and crpRanges from the Pim session.
Disable the given item provided by -handle
Enable the given item provided by -handle

restriction.value: create delete modify clear_all disable enable

description.text: PIM-SM session handle.
Groups to be added beforehand through procedure emulation_multicast_group_config. This parameter may be a list. If the case, all other parameters that can be lists should have the same list length.

Associate source pool(s) with the group. The source pool(s) must be added beforehand through procedure emulation_multicast_source_config. Specify one or more source pool handle(s) for (S,G) entries. None for (*,G) entries. If one or more are specified, source-specific join/prune will be enabled; otherwise it is disabled. This parameter may be a list. If the case, all other parameters that can be lists should have the same list length.

Group membership handle that associates a group pool with a PIM session. This option is returned from previous call to this proc with "create" mode. In "modify" mode, membership handle must be used in conjunction with the session handle to identify the member group pool. If this is a list, all other parameters that can be lists should have the same list length. As such, multiple router interfaces will be created with the given parameters.

This argument determines if individual interface, session or router handles are returned by the current command. This applies only to the command on which it is specified. Setting this to 0 means that only NGPF-specific protocol stack handles will be returned. This will significantly decrease the size of command results and speed up script execution. The default is 0, meaning only protocol stack handles will be returned.
This parameter represents the time interval (in seconds) between two consecutive Candidate RP advertisements.
The back off time interval for the C-RP-Adv messages.
Start address of the set of candidate RPs to be simulated.
The IP address of Rendezvous Point router for the multicast group pool. This parameter may be a list. If the case, all other parameters that can be lists should have the same list length.
The incrementing step for the IP address of Rendezvous Point router for the multicast group pool.

Specifies whether the membership pool is used to send or receive PIM messages. Note: no configuration required for receive mode. Valid choices are: send - Sends Join/Prunes (downstream DR) messages. register - Sends Register and NULL Register messages. (source DR) and receive Stop-Register messages. candidate_rp - Creates new Candidate Rendez-Vous.

choice.choiceText: Sends Register and NULL Register messages. (source DR) and receive Stop-Register messages.

description.text: If 1, enables the packing of multiple groups in a single packet; however, this option does not specify the exact number groups in a packet. This parameter may be a list. If the case, all other parameters that can be lists should have the same list length.

If true (1), enable wildcard group. When enabled, (*,*,RP) Join/ Prune messages are sent. Takes effect only if (S,G) is disabled. (no source pool). This parameter may be a list. If the case, all other parameters that can be lists should have the same list length. (DEFAULT = 0)

If true (1), enable (S,G,rpt). When enabled, (S,G,rpt) Join/Prune messages are sent. Takes effect only if (S,G) is enabled. Note: only one of s_g_rpt_group, register_triggered_sg, spt_switchover options can be enabled per multicast group. This parameter may be a list. If the case, all other parameters that can be lists should have the same list length. (DEFAULT = 0)
If true (1), enable rate control on Join/Prune and register messages.
The length of interval (in ms) during which a number of messages will be sent. If 0, send as fast as possible.
The number of Join/Prune messages sent per interval.
The number of Register messages sent per interval.
The number of Register Stop messages sent per interval.

If flap is enabled thru the emulation_pim_control, this is the amount amount of time, in seconds, between simulated flap events. (DEFAULT= 60)
Rate controlling variable indicating how many C-RP-Adv messages can be sent in the specified time interval.
Time interval after which priority of all the RPs get changed, if priority type is incremental or random.

priorityType This indicates the type of priority to be held by the candidate RPs (CRPs). One of: same - (default) CRPs send advertisement messages with time invariant fixed priority as specified in CRP Advertisement Message Priority. incremental - Priority starts from the configured value and with every Priority Change Interval, the CRPs priority get incremented by 1. random - The start value is selected based on a pseudorandom number generator with every Priority Change Interval, when sending the next batch of CRP-Adv messages.
Value of priority field sent in candidate RP advertisement messages.

The gap, in milliseconds, between periodically transmitted Register messages. This parameter may be a list. If the case, all other parameters that can be lists should have the same list length. (DEFAULT = 5000)

If register_triggered_sg option is enabled (1), this is the count of register messages received that will trigger transmission of a (S,G) message. This parameter may be a list. If the case, all other parameters that can be lists should have the same list length. (DEFAULT = 10)

The number of UDP destination ports in the receiving multicast group. This parameter may be a list. If the case, all other parameters that can be lists should have the same list length. (DEFAULT = 3000)

The number of UDP source ports sending encapsulated UDP packets to multicast groups via Register messages to the RP. This parameter may be a list. If the case, all other parameters that can be lists should have the same list length. (DEFAULT = 3000)

When enabled (1), sends (S,G) Join/Prune messages when matching registers have been received. Sends register stop after registerStopTriggerCount registers have been received. Note: only one of s_g_rpt_group, register_triggered_sg, spt_switchover options can be enabled per PIM group.
Total number of candidate RPs to be simulated starting from C-RP Address. A contiguous address range is used for this RP range simulation.

When enabled (1), Sends (*,G)->(S,G) switchover type. Indicates that the simulated router will switch over from a non-source specific group state to a source specific group state. Note: only one of s_g_rpt_group, register_triggered_sg, spt_switchover options can be enabled per PIM group. This parameter may be a list. If the case, all other parameters that can be lists should have the same list length.

Set the type of mapping that occurs when routes are advertised. This only applies for (S,G) and switchover types for MGR and is meaningful for RR. Choices are: fully_meshed, one_to_one. This parameter may be a list. If the case, all other parameters that can be lists should have the same list length.

The time interval, in seconds, allowed for the switch from using the RP tree to using a source-specific tree. Used when spt_switchover option is enabled. This parameter may be a list. If the case, all other parameters that can be lists should have the same list length. (DEFAULT = 0)

Enables the transmission of an initial null registration at emulation startup. This parameter may be a list. If the case, all other parameters that can be lists should have the same list length. (DEFAULT = 0)
The number of times CRP Advertisments is sent to the newly elected Bootstrap Router.
